			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">NaCl's TCB does mmap() in 64k chunks even on Unix, but this is unnecessary and slows things down.  mmap() only needs to operate in 64k chunks on Windows.

For example, see the loops that use NACL_MAP_PAGESIZE in nacl_desc_imc_shm.c.
